        <title>Linux server hard disk Raid installation</title>
        <link>https://tsairongfu.github.io/en/p/linux-server-raid/</link>
        <pubDate>Sat, 11 Sep 2021 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
        
        <guid>https://tsairongfu.github.io/en/p/linux-server-raid/</guid>
        <description>&lt;img src="https://tsairongfu.github.io/en/p/linux-server-raid/Pickering%27s%20Triangle%20-%20HOO.png" alt="Featured image of post Linux server hard disk Raid installation" /&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;error&#34;&gt;Error&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://askubuntu.com/questions/973632/unable-to-mount-raid1-md0-wrong-fs-type-bad-option-bad-superblock-on-dev-md&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;Reference Article&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Unable to Mount RAID1 md0 - wrong fs type, bad option, bad superblock on /dev/md0, missing codepage or helper program, or other error&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;mount-the-volume&#34;&gt;mount the volume&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;code&gt;sudo mount /home/Raid6&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;code&gt;sudo mount /dev/sdb* /path&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;view-disk-instructions&#34;&gt;View disk instructions&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;sudo blkid&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;sudo fdisk -l&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;sudo fdisk -l /dev/sd*&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;df&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;##Format the hard drive&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;sudo mkfs.ext4 /dev/sd*&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;configure-boot-self-mounting&#34;&gt;Configure boot self-mounting&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;sudo nano /etc/fstab&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Write configuration file example&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;UUID=e8d9acdd-4161-4efc-9ad1-7907e6a339a4 /path ext4 defaults 0 1&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;mount&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;sudo mount -a&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
        </item>
        <item>
        <title>Linux system partition space configuration</title>
        <link>https://tsairongfu.github.io/en/p/linux-system-space-size-configuration/</link>
        <pubDate>Sat, 24 Jul 2021 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
        
        <guid>https://tsairongfu.github.io/en/p/linux-system-space-size-configuration/</guid>
        <description>&lt;img src="https://tsairongfu.github.io/en/p/linux-system-space-size-configuration/Moar%20M31.jpg" alt="Featured image of post Linux system partition space configuration" /&gt;&lt;h1 id=&#34;boot&#34;&gt;/boot&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Select the free area, click the &amp;ldquo;+&amp;rdquo; sign to add the boot partition:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Size: 400MB&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Type of new partition: primary partition&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The location of the new partition: the starting location of the space&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;for: Ext4 journaling filesystem&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mount point: /boot&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h1 id=&#34;swap&#34;&gt;swap&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;ol start=&#34;2&#34;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continue to select the free area, click the &amp;ldquo;+&amp;rdquo; sign to add the swap partition, and set it to 2 times the actual memory:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Size: 8192MB (4GB×2)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Type of new partition: logical partition&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The location of the new partition: the starting location of the space&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;for: swap space&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h1 id=&#34;home&#34;&gt;/home&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;ol start=&#34;4&#34;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continue to select the free area, click the &amp;ldquo;+&amp;rdquo; sign to add the home partition:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Size: all the space left&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Type of new partition: logical partition&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The location of the new partition: the starting location of the space&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;for: Ext4 journaling filesystem&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mount point: /home&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h1 id=&#34;heading&#34;&gt;/&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;ol start=&#34;3&#34;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continue to select the free area, click the &amp;ldquo;+&amp;rdquo; sign to add the root partition:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Size: at least 10-20GB&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Type of new partition: logical partition&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The location of the new partition: the starting location of the space&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;for: Ext4 journaling filesystem&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;mount point: /&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;install-the-bootloader-device&#34;&gt;Install the bootloader device&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you want to use the Ubuntu bootloader instead of the Windows bootloader, choose /dev/sda.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you want to keep the Windows bootloader, select the /boot partition.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
</description>
        </item>
